Art---should we send business into a country that isn't democratic?   Really tough call.  Everything you say is true and the counter-aargument is we can't affect the situation if we are not there.<br>
    After my travels I--reluctantly come down on the side of being there---but with a large BUT.  The BUT using the power that presence provides to change the situation.  That's were it usually falls down.  You hear &quot;if we do 'that' then look at the jobs/money we'll lose if......&quot;<br>
    Following that logic is moral bankrupcy and one we follow all too often.  It comes down to using the power we have---on the theory that it will hurt them more then us and they will cave.  They usaully will, but only if we have the courage to push.<br><br>
